{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1516449574,"nonce":"KSOCBcltkzNW6rs03gjoywf/bxA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyOTAxODcxMzQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1676","origin":"github"},"title":"RFC: auto-update tools","message":"Given conda packages and the easy retrieval of all packages and there versions (`check_output(\"wget --quiet https://conda.anaconda.org/%s/%s/repodata.json.bz2 -O '%s.bz2' \u0026\u0026 bzip2 -d '%s.bz2'\" % (channel, platform_tag, repo_data, repo_data))`) it should be possible to watch selected Galaxy tools and upgrade the dependencies to fit the conda version.\n\n1. annotate selected tools (bowtie, hisat, fastqc ...) in the shed.yaml file with `auto_update: True`\n2. use https://github.com/galaxyproject/planemo-monitor to also track shed.yaml files\n3. upgrade the tool-requirements, the tool-version and submit a PR\n    - I don't think we should do much magic here, we can define some standards that makes it easier to find the spots that needs to be changed (`@WRAPPER_VERSION@, @TOOL_VERSION@` ...)\n    - submitting a PR automatically is already implemented and used in https://github.com/galaxyproject/planemo-monitor\n\nIdeally this should be implemented in planemo with a new sub-command.\nAnyone up for this task?","files":null}]}